The paper discusses the development of a conditional generative model using neural networks for longitudinal data generation, with a focus on neuroimaging studies. This involves incorporating a recurrent subnetwork and context gating to include smooth transitions in a sequence of generated data. Given this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these are all relevant to the development of generative models using neural networks. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible sub-categories, as they are relevant to the use of neural networks and natural language processing in the paper's methodology.
